<title>UK: Nomura increases Euro Note Programme to $3.0 bln.</title>
<headline>Nomura increases Euro Note Programme to $3.0 bln.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-02-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Nomura Bank International Plc has increased its $2.0 billion Euro Note Programme to $3.0 billion, Nomura said in a statement.</p>
<p>&quot;Our programme, initiated in 1994 and increased in 1995 has proved extremely successful prompting us to issue a further $1.0 billion of notes,&quot; NBI managing director Seiichi Takeda said in the statement.</p>
<p>&quot;The Programme has enabled NBI to reduce our cost of funding and has also provided us with long term deposits.&quot;</p>
<p>-- London Newsroom +44 171 542 7718</p>
